9 SECTION 10. IC 34-24-6.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
10 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
11 JULY 1, 2026]:
12 Chapter 6.5. Deed Fraud
13 Sec. 1. As used in this chapter, "mortgage" means a mortgage
14 or mortgage lien on an interest in real property in Indiana given to
15 secure a loan.
16 Sec. 2. A person that alleges damages arising from the recording
17 of a forged deed or mortgage has a cause of action against any of
18 the following persons:
19 (1) The person who forged the signature of the person alleging
20 damages arising from the recording of a forged deed or
21 mortgage on a deed or mortgage.
22 (2) A person who, with actual knowledge that the deed or
23 mortgage included a forged signature, submitted the deed or
24 mortgage to a county recorder for recording under
25 IC 32-21-2.
26 (3) A person with actual knowledge that the title to the real
27 property is based on a forged deed, and who purports to sell
28 or encumber the property to someone who is unaware of the
29 forged deed.
30 Sec. 3. A plaintiff who prevails in an action under this chapter
31 is entitled to reasonable attorney's fees and compensatory and
32 punitive damages.
33 SECTION 11. IC 34-30-2.1-521.3 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
34 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
35 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 521.3. IC 32-21-2-17 (Concerning
36 the recording of an instrument).
